                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On April 24, the United States introduced in the United Nations Disarmament
                    Commission a proposal on Essential Principles for a Disarmament Program. The
                    proposal was circulated as UN doc. <gloss target="#t_DC1">DC</gloss>/C.1/1. For
                    text, see <hi rend="italic">Documents on Disarmament, 1945–1959</hi>, volume I,
                    pages 357–358. For statements made by <persName corresp="#p_COHENBV1">Benjamin
                        V. Cohen</persName>, Deputy United States Representative on the Disarmament
                    Commission, in Committee I of the Commission regarding the proposal and the
                    general United States position, see Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, May 12, 1952, pages 752–753. For certain remarks <pb
                        facs="0082" n="896" xml:id="pg_896"/> by <persName corresp="#p_COHENBV1"
                        >Cohen</persName> before Committee II of the Commission on April 25, see <hi
                        rend="italic">ibid</hi>., pages 753–755.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
